<p>I use Azure Mobile Service and I try to execute this query :</p>  <pre><code>var interventions = await _interventionRemoteTable.Where(inter =&gt; inter.Logement.IdLogement == idLogement).ToListAsync(); </code></pre>  <p>An error occurs each time : The member 'IdLogement' is not supported in the 'Where' Azure Mobile Services query</p>  <p>If I make this request in two steps (by getting all "Interventions" first and then filtering local), it works.</p>  <pre><code>var interventions = await _interventionRemoteTable.ToListAsync();  var result = interventions.Where(inter =&gt; inter.Logement.IdLogement == idLogement); </code></pre>  <p>Of course, this is not what I want. I want the filtering is done on the server in order to not get thousands of data.</p>  <p>Is there a method for filtering on a navigation property?</p>  <p>Thanks,</p>